place.name: STICKFORD
place.gazetteerText: STICKFORD, a parish, with a village, in Spilsby district, Lincoln; 5 miles WNW of Eastville r. station, and 6 SW of Spilsby. Post town, Boston. Acres, 670. Real property, £2,565. Pop., 357. Houses, 80. The property is much subdivided. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £175.* Patron, the Bishop of L. The church is good, and has a lofty ancient tower. There are chapels for Wesleyans and Primitive Methodists, and an endowed school with £8 a year. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
